The company is requesting funding of $770,000 for short-term working capital necessary to assist fruit producers in Mexico for shipments into United States and Canada. The company currently a well-known and trusted brokerage firm for some of the most successful and well-respected growers in the entire Mexican region, providing integrated Sales, Marketing, and Consulting services to assist growers sell their crops with a minimum of headaches, and maximum profits. Jim Pandol & Co’s experience in farming and agricultural markets; and commitment to their growers and customers is the key to their success, and the reason for the current expansion and additional funding requirements. The primary goal of Jim Pandol & Co. is to expand our, already successful, operation in a manner that deepens our business relationships with our growers in Mexico and Southern California; while effectively providing our investors an adequate return on their investment. During the initial phase of the investment, our company will assist our growers through the planting, raising, cultivating, harvesting, packing and shipping of the extra sweet grapes, honeydew melons, fresh and frozen strawberries products the company intends to market for sale to its Grocery Store Customers.  Crops are produced in cycles according to their season. Some growers need financial help at time of planting; others do not need outside financing until time of harvest and shipping.

Description: FIT Bearings manufactures products such as ball bearings, mounted units, wheel hubs, oil seals and sprockets.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Founded in 1988 and incorporated in 1990, FIT Bearings' corporate office is located in Fremont, California, southwest of San Francisco in the Silicon Valley vicinity. The company began sourcing Tapered Roller Bearings out of Dalian, China, in 1989. Thier mounted units line was launched in 1991 out of Henan, China. In 1992, They started stocking ball bearings from multiple factories, including products from one of the largest bearing manufacturers located in Harbin, China. Taiwanese Oil Seals were introduced to the U.S market in 1993, and the FIT Bearings brand trademark was registered in the U.S. in 1994. By 1995, FIT Bearings had become a standard name in the bearing industry and was listed in the most comprehensive guide available, The I.B.I. guide (International Bearing Interchange). This guide allows the company to cross-reference bearings, mounted units, seals, drive belts, and filters quickly and easily. With brands such as Browning, NTN, Torrington, SKF, Timken, NSK, and more, FIT Bearings was honored to be listed alongside such prestigious bearing manufacturers.

You can join the group at www.nyetm.com, and view videos of past presentations there as well. The Meetup was launched as a way to help the enterprise technology ecosystem in NY leverage the great foundation set by its consumer counterpart.  Consumer technology has a strong community including incubators, meetups such as the NYTM, and many networking opportunities, and the NYETM aims to become a first class enterprise cohort. Description: U-Subs Deli will be the first quick serve restaurant to serve vertical subs.
Full Description: U-Subs Deli will be the first quick serve restaurant to serve vertical subs. A vertical Sub is a sub that uses an unsliced bread roll which is cored out and toasted than stuffed and served standing up (vertically). There are a few full service restaurants around the country selling vertical subs and doing very well but none have developed a patented tool to insert the ingredients like we have. We can make a sub using our special toaster and loading tool in under 30 seconds which is ideal for a drive thru concept.
